  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To simplify and improve the diagnostic approach to patients with clinically suspected
      recurrent DVT by determining whether the results of the combination of IPG and d-dimer
      testing, using a whole blood agglutination assay, can be used in the management of such
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
